This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on detecting metaphorical word use in context. Additionally, the use of BiLSTM models is a common technique in NLP research, further supporting this categorization. 

The paper also involves the use of neural models, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of benchmarks and evaluation metrics, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the analysis of linguistic context, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
